        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:59PM AST by NWS San Juan PR</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM AST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Lares, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly areas of northern Sabana Grande,
Las Marias, southern Lares, southern San Sebastian, northwestern
Adjuntas, southern Moca, northwestern Yauco, Anasco, Maricao,
northeastern Mayaguez, Rincon, southwestern Utuado, Aguada and
southwestern Aguadilla Municipalities, including the following
locations... Espino, Maricao, and Stella.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
